23/12/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- President Filip Vujanovic starts consulting on Thursday (December 23rd) with leaders of the various political parties in parliament about who will succeed Milo Djukanovic as prime minister.
He stepped down on Tuesday.
According to the constitution, the president nominates the prime minister after these consultations and parliament approves the candidate.
The ruling Democratic Party of Socialists has already tapped Finance Minister Igor Luksic for the post.
He has said that his main priority -- if elected -- will be to guarantee the start of EU accession talks.
(Mina, TV IN, Mina, RTCG, Portal Analitika - 22/12/10)
